folder: Coenties Slip & Water Street, Manhattan, NY
text: Coenties Slip, north side, east from and including Water Street, to but not including Front Street. This view also shows Water Street, north from Coenties Slip. September 20, 1929. P.L. Sperr
title: Manhattan: Coenties Slip - Water Street

folder: Coenties Slip & Water Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
(1)

Coenties Slip, north side, east from and including Water, to and including Front Streets, showing a general view northward, from No. 115 Broad Street, at the S.E. corner of Front Street, with a portion of the Second and Third Ave. Elevated in the foreground. Also shown is Front Street, east side, north from but not including
Coenties Slip, to and including Wall Street.

November 2, 1931.

P. L. Sperr.

(2)

The same, from a different angle.

P. L. Sperr.

October 9, 1935.

folder: Coenties Slip & Water Street, Manhattan, NY
text:
Coenties Slip, north side, west from Water (right) to Pearl (left) Streets, showing the South Ferry Division of the 2nd & 3rd Avenues Elevated Lines making an "S" turn on the Slip; the train (on the left) being South Ferry bound, after coming out of Pearl Street. No. 1 is an enlargement by the photographer; No. 2 being a copy of the original negative by the N.Y.P.L.

About 1936.

Gift of Dr. Michael Wishengrad A.R.P.S.
title: Manhattan: Coenties Slip - Water Street

folder: Water Street & Coenties Slip, Manhattan, NY
text:
43-47 Water Street, at, adjoining and north of the N.E. corner of Coenties Slip. Also shown is No. 10 Coenties Slip, at the N.E. corner of Water Street, which is the same building.

June 5, 1936.

P. L. Sperr.

ASSUMING STREET TO BE NORTH AND SOUTH
